HEADWORD: Wharling
<hw>Wharl"ing</hw>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A guttural pronunciation of the letter <it>r</it>; a
burr. See <er>Burr</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 6.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A strange, uncouth <qex>wharling</qex> in their speech.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

